entry.title: Yeh Gulistan Hamara
entry.content: Vijay (Dev Anand), a young and dynamic civil engineer, is assigned with the tasks of bridging the gap between Indian and Chinese villages by constructing a bridge between the two villages. This bridge was going to help them socially as well as economically, but the villagers on both sides of the border didn’t want the bridge to be constructed. Vijay managed to convince the villagers on the Indian side to help in constructing the bridge. But the Chinese villager’s objected to the bridge under the command of their crooked ruler, Deng Do Rani (Pran), who didn’t want to have good relations with India. The construction of the bridge started with the help of villagers on the Indian side but to destroy progress, Deng Do Rani sends his goons to disrupt their work and threaten Vijay. But on the contrary Vijay falls in love with one of his goons, Soo Reni (Sharmila Tagore). Soo Reni also falls in love with Vijay and is moved by the benefits of the bridge after Vijay explains it to her. Deng Do Rani grows furious after he learns about Soo Reni’s betrayal and issues orders to kill her. Will Soo Reni survive the odds stacked against her? Can Vijay triumph in his mission to build a bridge and unite the two borders?

entry.title: Tyaagi - Rajnikanth, Mithun Chakraborty
entry.content: Jagdish (Mithun Chakraborty) lives a simple and honest life with his wife Savitri. Jagdish’s co-workers and cruel parents prey on his innocence and take advantage of him. Jagdish is tormented by corruption and atrocities around him and he transforms himself into a man of absolute power. He starts moonlighting as a vigilante named Alfred to fight crime and serve justice. A man named Ranjit sets his eyes on Savitri and schemes devious plans to break her marriage. What price will Jagdish pay to vanquish evil as Alfred? Can he save his wife before it’s too late?

entry.title: Tezaab
entry.content: Mahesh Deshmukh (Anil Kapoor) has joined the nation’s armed forces as that he can honestly and patriotically serve the country. During his college days he has a run-in with fellow-collegian Mohini (Madhuri Dixit). A bet between his friends and himself ends up with him falling in love with Mohini, who subsequently realizes that he indeed has fallen in love with her, and she too reciprocates. Mohini’s dad (Anupam Kher) is an alcoholic and wishes that Mohini takes up dancing and prostitution so that he can get his daily dose of alchol. Mohini attempts to take refuge with Mahesh, however, cirumstances tangle Mahesh to such an extent that he is arrested, charged, and sentenced to stay away from Bombay city limits. When Mahesh returns, it is no longer the honest, and patriotic Mahesh, but a gangster named Munna, who has many old scores to settle.

entry.title: Swarg Yahan Narak Yahan
entry.content: Vijay (Mithun Chakraborty) is an honest police officer married to Suman (Sumalatha). Several years after their marriage, Suman gives birth to Suraj, and Suman spoils Suraj as he is their only son. As a result Suraj grows up to be a brat, falls into bad company and Vijay is forced to send Suraj to a distant Boarding school. Suraj grows up in the boarding school with hatred for his father and years later he return home. Suraj meets Haveli Ram (Gulshan Grover), father of his childhood rich friend Bharat. Haveli Ram ropes in Suraj for his drug smuggling ring and uses his fathers house as a secret hideout for the illegal activity. Time comes when this treachery gets exposed and Vijay must decide the fate of his only son. But with Suraj continuing on the path of destruction, what will Vijay do?

entry.title: Sharmilee
entry.content: Captain Ajit (Shashi Kapoor) crosses paths with young and energetic Kamini (Rakhee) in Kashmir and instantly falls in love with her. After a brief romance, Kamini disappears leaving Ajit in despair of ever seeing her again. Meanwhile, Ajit’s guardian, Father Joseph (Nazir Hussein) seeks to arrange Ajit’s marriage to Kamini’s twin sister, Kanchan (Rakhee in double role), not knowing Ajit has fallen for Kamini. Ajit agrees to the marriage mistaking Kanchan to be Kamini but when the truth comes out, Ajit insists on marrying Kamini, leaving Kanchan heart-broken. Things take a violent turn when Kundan (Ranjeet) a villain from Kamini’s past surfaces and threatens to destroy her. Kundan attacks Kamini but ends up getting murdered. In a race to dispose Kundan’s body, Kamini meets with an accident and her car falls off a cliff. Presumed dead, Kamini’s parents make Kanchan to pose as Kamini and marry her off to Ajit. Is Kamini dead? What happens when the truth gets exposed?

entry.title: Shandaar
entry.content: Shanker (Mithun Chakraborty) belongs to a poor family, and is living with his brother Ashok (Sumeet Saigal) and his mother in a village. Shanker works as a woodcutter to fulfill the needs of his family and wants his brother to study and become a big man, so he sends him to a college in Mumbai to complete his studies. Shanker meets Rani (Meenakshi Sheshadri), who comes from a missle class family background and they both fall in love. Shanker finds an admirer in Anita Chaurasia (Mandakini), who is a daughter of a multimillionaire industrialist and politician Rai Bahadur Arjun Chaurasia (Kader Khan). Shanker finds out about Arjun’s illegal work done and decides to expose him. While Arjun gets to know about Shanker’s plan about exposing him, he hires a gangster named Dhaga (Danny Denzongpa) to get him killed. Will Shanker be able to expose Arjun to the people in the village? Will Dhaga be able to succeed in killing Shanker?
